  {
    "id": "koc2012-q036",
    "type": "mcq",
    "topic": "databases",
    "subtopic": "ms-access",
    "stem": "For what is a Relationship window used in Access?",
    "options": [
      {
        "label": "A",
        "text": "To define a relationship between tables & queries.",
        "isCorrect": true
      },
      {
        "label": "B",
        "text": "To define a relationship between reports.",
        "isCorrect": false
      },
      {
        "label": "C",
        "text": "To define a relationship between forms",
        "isCorrect": false
      }
    ],
    "answerOptionLabels": [
      "A"
    ],
    "explanation": "The Relationships window defines joins between the objects that hold data, linking a primary key in one table to a foreign key in another (queries can also be placed there). Forms and reports only display data, so they have no relationships to define, which rules out B and C.",
    "source": {
      "file": "KOC 2012 EXAM (2).pdf",
      "exam": "KOC",
      "tier": "bank",
      "year": 2012,
      "originalNumber": 36
    },
    "keyProvenance": "inline_bold",
    "keyVerified": true,
    "verificationLevel": "single",
    "needsReview": false,
    "flags": [
